==English==
===Noun===
'''sagger''' <br />
1. A [[box]] or [[casing]] of clay used to protect delicate [[ceramic]]s during [[fire|firing.]]

2. [[slang|Slang]] term for a young male, who wears [[trousers]] very low on his [[hip]]s, exposing [[underwear]] and/or his [[buttocks]] or lower abdominals.

3. The [[w:NATO|NATO]] designation for a [[Soviet]] AT-3 series man-portable, wire-guided [[missile]] first deployed in the 1960's.

